DAMATURU – Elected Councilors of Fika Local Government Area have today passed vote of confidence on the leadership of Halima Kyari Joda, the Chairperson. The majority leader of the Council announced during a press briefing at the local government Secretariat in Fika town. According to him, “on 21st March, 2022 some of our workers that includes the supervisory Councilors, Council Secretary and Vice Chairman sat and criticized our Council Chairperson. We felt bad because they did such to spoil the name of the local government because Hajiya Halima Kyari Joda is a lady like man that is recognized for hardwork and Yobe is proud of her, that is what gingered us to gather here in order to take a measure against them”. “The allegation that the Chairperson travelled abroad without permission is not true”. He explained that “The Speaker of the Council has just set up a five-man committee who will invite the aggrieved to ask them on their reason for condemning her, then we take a necessary action.” “The committee will be chaired by the Deputy Speaker- Nuhu Daya, Adamu Ibrahim will serve as the Secretary of the committee while Sale Adamu Bagade, Inusa Mubi Fusami and Abubakar Bello Kawuwa members respectively”.